    "content": "Chandelier - Sia\r\nTabbed by: Bree\r\nE-mail: bgward65@yahoo.com\r\nTuning: Standard\r\n\r\nVerse: No playing.\r\n\r\n[tab][Pre-Chorus]\r\n(Come in at \"1, 2, 3...\". Stop at \"Throw 'em back...\")\r\nG|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\nD|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\nA|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\nE|---2222222--4444444--1111111-----------------------------------------------|[/tab]\r\n\r\n[tab][Chorus]\r\n(Personally, I strum like I would an acoustic guitar, alternating up and down\r\nbut you don't have to. Listen to the beat and play to it.)\r\nPlay from \"I'm gonna swing...\". Pause at 1:16 when she says the last \"chandelier\"\r\nG|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\nD|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\nA|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\nE|---2222222--4444444--1111111--2222222----(x4)------------------------------|[/tab]\r\n\r\n[tab][Post-Chorus]\r\n\"But, I'm holding on for dear life...\" up through the final \"on for tonight.\"\r\nG|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\nD|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\nA|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\nE|---2222222--4444444--1111111--2222222----(x2)------------------------------|[/tab]\r\n\r\nRepeat through the whole song. Very simple, fun, and easy to play <3\r\n\r\nENJOY! :)",
